## 1. Monetization: $49/month is the market's default entry price

### Competitive pricing landscape

The GEO audit tool market has settled into clear pricing tiers. **Geoptie** leads the GEO-specific category at **$49/month** (Starter) with 7 free tools requiring no signup. **Peec AI** starts at **€85/month** with 50 tracked prompts across 3 AI models — they hit €650K ARR within four months of launch. **Scrunch AI** targets enterprise at **$300–$500/month**. WordLift's new Agent Plan runs **€160/month** annually.

The closest architectural comp to GEO-Pulse is **SEOptimer**, which proves the freemium audit model works at scale: unlimited free basic audits, then **$29/month** (DIY SEO), **$39/month** (White Label with branded PDF reports), and **$59/month** (White Label + Embedding with lead-gen widget). Their entire funnel — free audit → subscription conversion — is the template GEO-Pulse should follow.

Traditional SEO suites price significantly higher: **Ahrefs Lite** at $129/month, **Semrush Pro** at $139.95/month. Ahrefs added a new **$29/month Starter** tier in January 2026 (a 70% price cut from their old entry), signaling downward pressure. **Ubersuggest** remains the outlier with $12–40/month plans and lifetime purchases at $120–$400.

### Conversion rates and pricing model

Industry data from First Page Sage's 2026 report across 86 SaaS companies shows **freemium-to-paid conversion rates of 2.6–2.8%** for self-serve products, with good performers hitting 6–8% and great ones exceeding 10%. Free trials with credit-card-required convert at **~25%**. For a URL-input GEO audit tool, plan on **3% as your baseline** conversion rate.

**Subscription has decisively won over one-time reports.** No major SEO or GEO audit tool sells one-time reports as a SaaS product. SEOptimer charges $29–59/month for unlimited audits. Geoptie gives unlimited reports on every plan. The math is simple: a $49/month subscriber yields **$588/year** at 12-month retention versus $49 total from a one-time report. However, a **one-time "Deep GEO Audit" upsell at $49–99** works well as a conversion accelerator alongside the subscription.

### Agency white-label sweet spot

Agencies charge their clients **$2,500–$15,000** for one-time GEO audits and **$500–$10,000/month** for ongoing retainers. The tool-cost sweet spot is **$59–99/month** for white-label access, letting agencies maintain 80%+ margins. Key features agencies require: custom branding on PDF reports, embeddable audit widget for lead generation, custom domain, Zapier/webhook integration, and multi-client management.

### Recommended GEO-Pulse pricing

