## 2. The $0 tech stack: verified limits that define your ceiling

Every number below was confirmed against official documentation in March 2026. These limits are your architectural constraints — design around them, not against them.

### Cloudflare Workers (free tier)

| Resource | Limit |
|----------|-------|
| Requests/day | **100,000** (resets midnight UTC) |
| CPU time/invocation | **10 ms** (CPU time, not wall clock) |
| Subrequests/request | 50 |
| Script size | 3 MB compressed |
| KV reads/day | 100,000 |
| KV writes/day | 1,000 |
| KV storage | 1 GB |

**Critical gotcha:** The 10ms CPU limit is the hardest constraint. Waiting on `fetch()` calls doesn't count, but any computation does. PDF generation and complex LLM response parsing will exceed this. On the **paid tier ($5/month)**, CPU time jumps to 30 seconds — this is likely your first forced upgrade.

**Durable Objects** are available on the free plan but only with the SQLite storage backend. **Cloudflare Queues** gained a free tier in early 2026: **10,000 operations/day** with up to 10,000 queues and 24-hour retention. This is critical for async scan processing. Verify this in your dashboard, as this was a recent addition and documentation may lag.

### Cloudflare Pages (free tier)

Commercial use is **explicitly allowed**. Bandwidth and requests are **unlimited** with no stated cap. You get 500 builds/month, 100 sites, 100 custom domains per project. Pages Functions count toward your Workers quota. This is the most generous free hosting tier available.

### Supabase (free tier)

| Resource | Limit |
|----------|-------|
| Database size | **500 MB** |
| API calls | Unlimited |
| Auth MAUs | 50,000 |
| File storage | 1 GB |
| Edge Function invocations | 500,000/month |
| Realtime connections | 200 concurrent |
| Bandwidth | ~2 GB egress |

**Two production-killing gotchas.** First, projects **pause after 7 days of inactivity** — you must keep the project alive with a cron job or health-check endpoint. Second, the **2 GB bandwidth limit** can be exhausted in days with moderate traffic (500 DAU × 20 API calls × 50 KB = 500 MB/day). No automated backups exist on the free tier. Plan your migration to the $25/month Pro tier early.

### Resend (free tier)

**100 emails/day**, 3,000/month, 1 custom domain, 5 requests/second API rate limit. The daily cap means you're limited to ~100 audit report emails per day. Data retention is only 1 day on free. This was upgraded from 100/month to 3,000/month in 2024.

### Gemini 2.5 Flash-Lite (free tier — best free LLM option)

| Model | RPM | RPD | TPM |
|-------|-----|-----|-----|
| Gemini 2.5 Flash-Lite | 15 | **1,000** | 250,000 |
| Gemini 2.5 Flash | 10 | 250 | 250,000 |
| Gemini 2.5 Pro | 5 | 100 | 250,000 |

Google cut free tier limits by 50–80% in December 2025 — these are the post-cut stabilized numbers. **Flash-Lite at 1,000 requests/day is your workhorse.** Use Flash (250 RPD) for complex reasoning and Pro (100 RPD) sparingly. No credit card required. Free tier data may be used for Google product improvement — upgrading to Tier 1 (just enable billing) removes this. Claude and OpenAI have no comparable free API tiers.

### Stripe

No monthly fee, no setup fees, no minimums. **2.9% + $0.30** per successful card charge. Stripe Billing adds 0.5% on recurring charges. Purely pay-as-you-go.

### n8n and automation hosting at $0

n8n Cloud has **no permanent free tier** — only a 14-day trial. Railway offers only a **$5 trial credit**, not a permanent free tier. Render's free tier spins down after 15 minutes of inactivity with 30-second cold starts, making it unreliable for webhook-based automation.

The real $0 path: **self-host n8n on Oracle Cloud's Always Free Tier** — 4 OCPU ARM, 24 GB RAM, 200 GB storage. This is genuinely free forever and runs n8n comfortably 24/7. Alternative: Google Cloud's free e2-micro instance (0.25 vCPU, 1 GB RAM) works but is tight. Open-source alternatives to Make.com include **Automatisch**, **Activepieces** (has a limited free cloud tier), and **Windmill**.

### PDF generation in Cloudflare Workers

Puppeteer cannot run in V8 isolates. **pdf-lib** is the production-ready choice — pure JavaScript, runs in Workers, supports custom fonts, form filling, and merging. It handles programmatic PDF construction within the 10ms CPU limit for simple reports. **jsPDF** works but produces low-quality output with limited font support. For styled reports, the **Satori + resvg-wasm → pdf-lib pipeline** converts JSX-like markup to SVG to PDF, producing beautiful output but potentially exceeding free-tier CPU limits. On the $5/month paid plan, **Cloudflare Browser Rendering** (Puppeteer/Playwright) gives full HTML/CSS-to-PDF at ~6 seconds per invocation.

