## 5. Growth loops: build virality into the product, not around it

### The "share your score" mechanic is your primary growth engine

Build a visual scorecard (0–100 with letter grade) with a pre-generated Open Graph image that unfurls on social platforms. Include one-click share buttons with pre-populated copy: *"My site scored 72/100 on GEO readiness 🤖 Check yours →"*. Add a competitive element: *"You scored better than 68% of sites in your industry."* **Design the scoring rubric so most sites score 40–65/100** — this triggers both ego (high scorers brag) and anxiety (low scorers share seeking validation).

### Embeddable widget: the B2B growth loop that compounds

Provide a white-label JavaScript embed that agencies paste onto their websites. The widget shows a "Check your GEO readiness" form with URL input and email capture. Results are gated behind email — the agency gets the lead, GEO-Pulse gets brand exposure via a "Powered by GEO-Pulse" footer link. This is exactly how HubSpot Website Grader, Moz, and Ahrefs grew — embeddable widgets on agency sites created thousands of backlinks. Revenue model: free with branding → paid to remove branding or add agency logo.

### Cold outreach reality check

**Apollo.io's free tier** offers 10,000 email credits/month with ~250/day fair use limits and 2 active sequences. **Hunter.io** gives just 25 email searches/month but 500 campaign recipients. **Instantly.ai has no free tier** (starts at $37/month). **Lemlist's free plan** finds contacts but cannot send campaigns.

The honest assessment: cold email at $0 is marginal. You need 3–5 sending domains (~$50 total), 4–6 weeks of warming, and expect 1–3% response rates. At 250 emails/day via Apollo, that's ~75–225 responses per month. **Building in public, community participation, and the share-your-score loop will outperform cold outreach** per hour invested.

### SEO content strategy

Target both "GEO" and "AI SEO" keywords — the latter has more current volume but GEO is where the category is heading. High-intent long-tail queries to target: "Is my site GEO ready," "GEO readiness checker," "how to optimize for AI search," "ChatGPT SEO checker," "AI Overviews optimization tool." Comparison pages ("GEO-Pulse vs Surfer SEO") convert visitors who are already in decision mode. Programmatic SEO (city/niche pages like "GEO readiness for dentists in Austin") works but has a **60% failure rate** without 500+ unique words and 30%+ content differentiation per page.

### Free distribution channels worth the effort

Submit to every AI directory — **There's An AI For That**, **Toolify.ai**, **FutureTools**, **Futurepedia**, **AI Scout**. Each takes 5–10 minutes and provides both backlinks and discovery traffic. Submit to **Product Hunt** (launch Tuesday–Thursday at midnight PT, respond to every comment), **BetaList** (free submission takes 1–4 months), and **AlternativeTo**, **G2**, **Capterra**, **SaaSHub** for credibility signals. On Reddit (r/SEO, r/SaaS), become a genuine contributor first — share insights, not links. Hacker News Show HN rewards technical honesty and founder transparency.

