## 6. Building GEO-Pulse with Cursor: the vibe-coding blueprint

### Cursor rules have changed — `.cursorrules` is deprecated

Cursor now uses **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** files with YAML frontmatter instead of a single `.cursorrules` file. Create scoped rule files: `base.mdc` (always applied), `cloudflare.mdc` (scoped to worker files), `frontend.mdc` (scoped to components/app), `api.mdc` (scoped to API routes).

The best community template for this stack is from **PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules** — the `typescript-react-nextjs-cloudflare-cursorrules-pro` rule at `github.com/PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules`. Cloudflare also publishes an official AI prompt for Workers development at `developers.cloudflare.com/workers/get-started/prompting/`. Add **vibe-tools** (`github.com/eastlondoner/vibe-tools`) to extend Cursor with web search, repo analysis, and plan generation.

### Next.js on Cloudflare: use OpenNext, not next-on-pages

**`@cloudflare/next-on-pages` is deprecated.** The official path is now **`@opennextjs/cloudflare`**, which deploys Next.js to Cloudflare Workers (not Pages). Next.js 15 and 16 are fully supported with App Router, Server Components, Server Actions, ISR via R2 cache, and streaming SSR. Set `compatibility_date` to 2025-04-01 or later (required for `process.env` population) and enable the `nodejs_compat` flag. Watch bundle sizes — free tier limit is 3 MiB, paid is 10 MiB.

If you hit friction, **SvelteKit on Cloudflare Pages** is the most battle-tested alternative with the smoothest deployment experience.

### Build order optimized for momentum

**Phase 1 (Days 1–3):** Scaffold with `npm create cloudflare@latest -- geo-pulse --framework=next --experimental`. Set up `.cursor/rules/`. Configure wrangler.jsonc with D1 and KV bindings. Generate the landing page with Cursor agent mode. Define database schema with Drizzle ORM.

**Phase 2 (Days 4–7):** Authentication via **Better Auth** or **Clerk** (both work on Cloudflare — never let AI write auth from scratch). Stripe integration with Checkout and webhook handling. User dashboard skeleton.

**Phase 3 (Days 8–14):** The core GEO audit engine — analyze robots.txt for AI crawler access (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot), structured data/Schema.org markup, content extractability, citation signals, llms.txt presence, and technical SEO baseline. Results display with scoring. PDF report generation via pdf-lib.

**Phase 4 (Days 15–21):** Recurring audits via Cloudflare Queues. Share-your-score social proof. Email notifications via Resend. Embeddable widget for agencies.

