## Conclusion: the $0 ceiling and the $5 unlock

The viable $0 stack is: Cloudflare Pages (unlimited bandwidth) + Workers (100K requests/day) + Supabase (500 MB, keep alive with cron) + Resend (100 emails/day) + Gemini Flash-Lite (1,000 requests/day) + Stripe (pay per transaction) + n8n self-hosted on Oracle Cloud Free + pdf-lib for basic PDFs + Buffer Free (3 channels with unlimited AI).

Your first forced upgrade is **Cloudflare Workers paid at $5/month** — the 10ms CPU limit will break PDF generation and complex processing. Your second is **Supabase Pro at $25/month** when bandwidth or the inactivity-pause becomes untenable. Your third is **~$20–30/month for video and social scheduling** when you need professional faceless video and full platform coverage. Total runway to first revenue: approximately **$0 for MVP**, scaling to **~$55/month** once you need production reliability.

The GEO market is at an inflection point: mainstream enough for real demand, early enough that a free-tier auditor with a "share your score" viral loop can capture significant mindshare. Build the scoring rubric to make most sites uncomfortable with their score, embed the share mechanic into every interaction, and let the product do the selling. The founder stays invisible; the score is the brand.